### 10.

1\. While he was undergoing that Mânatta he

<span id="page_403">p. 403</span>

committed an offence--the first Sa*m*ghâdisesa which he did not conceal.

He told the Bhikkhus, saying, 'I committed, &c. . . . I asked the
Sa*m*gha. . . . The Sa*m*gha imposed \[&c., going through all that had
happened, down to the end of the first paragraph in this chapter\].

They told, &c.

'Let then the Sa*m*gha, O Bhikkhus, impose upon Udâyi the Bhikkhu a
Mânatta of six days' duration, throwing him back to the commencement (of
his Mânatta).

\[The kammavâ*k*â as before.\]

